text: East Yorkshire is an alternative name for the East Riding of Yorkshire, a county in Northern England. East Yorkshire could also be: *East Yorkshire (bus company) – formerly East Yorkshire Motor Services – a bus company in Yorkshire, England *East Yorkshire (district), a local government district of the county of Humberside, England, from 1981 to 1996 *East Yorkshire (UK Parliament constituency), created in 1997 *East Riding of Yorkshire (UK Parliament constituency) (1832-1885) *East Riding, York Shire, one of three ridings of York Shire (Province of New York) (1664-1683), now Suffolk County, New York
title: East Yorkshire (disambiguation)
